msgid "Forms As Cards"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:118
msgid ""
"RegistrationMagic displays all forms as rectangular cards. This is a novel "
"new approach. You will later see that a form card is much more than a "
"symbolic representation of a form. It can show you form related data and "
"stats at a glance."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:120
msgid ""
"All form cards are displayed as grid, starting from here. You may not need to "
"create more than one registrations form, but it's totally up to you. "
"RegistrationMagic gives a playground to experiment and play to find the best "
"combination for your site. First card slot is reserved for <b>Login Form</b>"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:121
msgid ""
"This is a form card. We automatically created it for you to give you a head "
"start."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:122
msgid ""
"This shows title of the form. When you create a new form, you can define its "
"title. You can always change title of this form later, by going into its "
"<b>General Settings</b>"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:123
msgid ""
"The checkbox on left side of the title allows you to select multiple forms "
"and perform batch operations. For example, deleting multiple forms. Of course "
"there's nothing stopping you from deleting or duplicating a single form."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:124
msgid ""
"Clicking this will open a popup menu allowing you direct access to different "
"sections of this form."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:125
msgid ""
"On top right side of each card is a red number badge. This is the count of "
"total times this form has been filled and submitted on your site by visitors."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:126
msgid ""
"This area displays 3 latest submissions for this form. On new forms it will "
"be empty in the start. Each submission will also show user's Gravatar and "
"time stamp."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_form_manager_old.php:127
msgid ""
"Now this is important. RegistrationMagic works through shortcodes. That "
"means, to display a form on the site, you must paste its shortcode inside a "
"page, post or a widget (where you want this form to appear). Form shortcodes "
"are always in this format - "
