#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:34
msgid "Using RegistrationMagic Widget"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:35
msgid ""
"If you are using one of the many available page builder plugins, you can also "
"use the built in RegistrationMagic widget to publish forms on your pages. "
"Page builder plugins allow you to create custom layouts by dragging and "
"dropping widgets in rows or columns. In Widgets section of your favorite page "
"builder plugin, search for 'RegistrationMagic Form' widget. Once selected, it "
"will ask you to select a form from dropdown in its settings. If you do not "
"find RegistrationMagic form widget, you can always add an editor widget and "
"paste RegistrationMagic form shortcode in it."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:37
msgid ""
"By using same method, you can also publish RegistrationMagic forms on any "
"widget area in your theme by going to Appearance -> Widgets section in your "
"dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:39
msgid "Using Front End sliding panel"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:40
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Turn on the Magic button on your site by going to <a target=\"_blank\" "
"href=\"%s\">Global Settings / General Settings</a>. Look for the toggle "
"checkbox with label <span class=\"rm-code\">Show Magic Pop-up Button, Menu "
"and Panels</span> and turn it on."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:41
msgid ""
"Make sure you have selected a form as your default registration form by "
"clicking on the grey star over the form card. This form will display "
"automatically inside the sliding panel."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:44
msgid "Embedding form on an external site"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:45
msgid ""
"This method to display registration forms on WordPress site is for advanced "
"users and therefore only available in Gold Bundle of RegistrationMagic. It "
"works best when we want to show a RegistrationMagic form where there’s no "
"option to paste the shortcode. For example – a site outside our WordPress "
"site."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:46
msgid "Embed codes are located just below the short code."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:54
msgid "How to insert a form into a post, page or widget?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:62
msgid ""
"The easiest way to insert a form into content is to paste its shortcode where "
"you want to display the form. Form shortcode is found on the form card. "
"RegistrationMagic form shortcodes are in this format"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:70
msgid "How to display a login box?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:79
msgid ""
"Login system is built into RegistrationMagic. To display a login box on any "
"page, post or widget use this code"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:87
msgid "How to allow users to check their submissions?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:96
msgid ""
"RegistrationMagic allows your website users to check the forms they have "
"submitted by logging into the front end area. Shortcode for front-end "
"submission viewing is <span class=\"rm-code\">[RM_Front_Submissions]</span>. "
"When the plugin is first installed a new page is automatically created with "
"this shortcode pasted inside it."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:104
msgid "How to let users check transaction details and status."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:111
msgid ""
"Front-end submission area also contains tab for transaction details. If you "
"have set up paid registration forms, then this area will display to users "
"with their transaction details including payments status as complete or "
"refunded."
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:117
msgid "Easily display list of registered users"
msgstr ""

#: admin/views/template_rm_frontend_primer.php:126
msgid ""
"Now you can display registered users' list on front end of your website! The "
"shortcode format is <span class=\"rm-code\">[RM_Users]</span>. This will "
"display all the users (registered through RegistrationMagic) on a page or "
"post where you paste the shortcode. If you want to display only specific "
"users, you can pass two more parameters to the shortcode - filter the list by "
"registration form and time of registration. The longer format is <span "
"class=\"rm-code\">[RM_Users form_id=\"id\" timerange=\"year\"]</span>. Where "
"id should be replaced by ID for the RegistrationMagic form and timerange can "
"be year, month, week or today. Of course, you can use any of the two "
"depending on your needs. IDs of the form can be found in their respective "
"form shortcodes."
msgstr ""

